org.afplib.helper.formdef

Interface Formdef


  • public interface Formdef
    Formdef is basically a collection of medium maps. Supports finding by various keys and adding (creating) new medium maps.

      • save

        void save(AfpOutputStream out,
          boolean asResource)
   throws IOException
        writes the formdef to the output stream, possibly encapsulating it in a BRS/ERS envelope. In this case the name of the resource will be F1INLINE.
        Parameters:
        out - afp file or formdef to write to.
        asResource - weather to wrap it into BRS/ERS
        Throws:
        IOException
